{"TopicId":192858,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Shuttle Challenge v6 - The STS thread [Stock and Mod Friendly] - ANNOUNCEMENT: v7 IS LIVE!","CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-02T08:43:32Z","PageNum":25,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-06T10:42:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was thinking about the orbital requirements of the fuel pod for STS-1b. As it is right now, the tolerances are\u00A0easier at higher altitudes, which is balanced by the increased difficulty in getting there. Still, I think most people stick to lower altitudes, and the tolerances are perhaps a bit too difficult. Plus the description could use some more cleaning up. So instead, I could replace the chart with an orbital eccentricity requirement. The eccentricity can be displayed with mods like \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E or MechJeb. I also derived a couple of formulae if you want to calculate it yourself. I could also create a public spreadsheet to do the calculation for you if there is demand for it.\u00A0Here are the formulae:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003ELet Pe be the periapsis as shown in map view\nLet Ap be the apoapsis as shown in map view\nLet r\u00A0be the radius of the central body (for Kerbin, r = 600 km)\nLet e be the eccentricity (e = 0 is perfectly circular, 0 \u0026lt; e \u0026lt; 1 is\u00A0elliptical, e = 1 is\u00A0parabolic, e\u00A0\u0026gt; 1 is hyperbolic)\n\nTo solve for e: e = (Ap - Pe) / (Ap \u002B Pe \u002B 2r)\n\nTo solve for Ap: Ap = ((Pe \u002B r)(1 \u002B e) / (1 - e)) - r\n\nTo solve for Pe: Pe = ((Ap \u002B r)(1 - e) / (1 \u002B e)) - r\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSetting the eccentricity requirement to 0.0001 regardless of altitude makes the challenge slightly easier up to 4000 km, and then harder past that. I\u0027m open to feedback before I make this an official rule. If you earned the badge already you won\u0027t be affected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-09-06T21:52:19Z\u0022 title=\u002209/06/2021 09:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 6, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by sturmhauke\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eadded formula to solve for Pe\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"QF9E","CreatedById":201203,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-06T20:53:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224028724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221630924920\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190611\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sturmhauke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, sturmhauke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe eccentricity can be displayed with mods like \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E or MechJeb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe eccentricity can also be displayed in the stock game, in the second tab in the gizmo in the lower left. I think it\u0027s a good idea to replace the current rules with the proposed eccentricity limit as it simplifies the mission rules.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-06T22:34:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI always forget that\u0027s there, but yes. I still use mods for celestial navigation; I feel they give better data for my needs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor reference, in case someone doesn\u0027t know what we\u0027re talking about:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022AyjCD2R.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002270.00\u0022 height=\u0022154\u0022 width=\u0022220\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/AyjCD2R.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Entropian","CreatedById":205453,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-07T04:00:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright, here\u0027s \u003Cs\u003EJool\u003C/s\u003E Saturn STS-1:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/3sGWpw7-lSM?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mission design was actually much easier than the Mars mission\u0027s.\u00A0 The hardest part was the ridiculously thick atmosphere - getting to orbit is really annoying because aero drag is still a thing so high up...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side note, I\u0027ve been looking through the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E configs for asteroid size and I think I can rescale them back to stock size.\u00A0 If I do that, I\u0027ll be able to do STS-9, as the \u0027roid colliders won\u0027t glitch out.\u00A0 Can I do this and still have it qualify as \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E?\u00A0 Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-07T05:29:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a nice video and a cool mission, good work! I\u0027ll review it more closely when I get a chance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you can make the asteroids work properly, you can do STS-9. The mission spec just says it has to be an asteroid, not how big it is. Most people go for little Class As anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-08T05:16:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/205453-entropian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022205453\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/205453-entropian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Entropian\u003C/a\u003E, I present to you the Saturn STS-1 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E badge. Another fine mission!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XfXRumb.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022114.68\u0022 height=\u0022125\u0022 width=\u0022109\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XfXRumb.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Entropian","CreatedById":205453,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-08T13:38:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-08T21:59:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224028664\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221630898803\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190611\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sturmhauke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/6/2021 at 5:26 AM, sturmhauke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll right, I believe I\u0027m finally fully caught up on the thread. Thanks for your help so far, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184444-artienia/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022184444\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/184444-artienia/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Artienia\u003C/a\u003E; if you don\u0027t mind sticking around a while so I can dive into some new missions, that\u0027d be great.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026gt;snip\u0026lt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be a pleasure to stay! i\u0027d love to see what new missions we could complete!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224029016\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221630987230\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205453\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Entropian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/7/2021 at 6:00 AM, Entropian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright, here\u0027s \u003Cs\u003EJool\u003C/s\u003E Saturn STS-1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026gt;snip\u0026lt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nman..... how do you keep making these? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Entropian","CreatedById":205453,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-09T00:59:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224029600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221631138357\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184444\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Artienia\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Artienia said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nman..... how do you keep making these?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA combination of dedication and insanity probably.\u00A0 I\u0027m not really sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T09:05:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA couple of announcements:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve updated the rule for STS-1b as discussed previously. If you\u0027ve already earned your badges, this doesn\u0027t affect you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn more exciting news, I\u0027ve reviewed \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022172132\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fulgora\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s Mun STS-2-4 mission more closely and decided to award a Skunkworks badge! Congratulations!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022W0Cdh2Y.jpg?1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002292.20\u0022 height=\u0022130\u0022 width=\u0022141\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/W0Cdh2Y.jpg?1\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-25T12:27:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036032\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632560727\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190611\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sturmhauke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, sturmhauke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA couple of announcements:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve updated the rule for STS-1b as discussed previously. If you\u0027ve already earned your badges, this doesn\u0027t affect you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn more exciting news, I\u0027ve reviewed \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022172132\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fulgora\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s Mun STS-2-4 mission more closely and decided to award a Skunkworks badge! Congratulations!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/W0Cdh2Y.jpg?1\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022W0Cdh2Y.jpg?1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002292.20\u0022 height=\u0022130\u0022 width=\u0022141\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/W0Cdh2Y.jpg?1\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongratulations \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022172132\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fulgora\u003C/a\u003E!\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fulgora","CreatedById":172132,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-28T21:36:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036032\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632560727\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190611\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sturmhauke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/25/2021 at 11:05 AM, sturmhauke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA couple of announcements:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve updated the rule for STS-1b as discussed previously. If you\u0027ve already earned your badges, this doesn\u0027t affect you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn more exciting news, I\u0027ve reviewed \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022172132\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fulgora\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s Mun STS-2-4 mission more closely and decided to award a Skunkworks badge! Congratulations!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/W0Cdh2Y.jpg?1\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022W0Cdh2Y.jpg?1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002292.20\u0022 height=\u0022130\u0022 width=\u0022141\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/W0Cdh2Y.jpg?1\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224036062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221632572839\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184444\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Artienia\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/25/2021 at 2:27 PM, Artienia said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongratulations \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022172132\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172132-fulgora/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Fulgora\u003C/a\u003E!\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWohoooooo \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot. I feel truly humbled to be one of the few recipients of this badge!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will do my best to prove that I am worthy of this honor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe design phase of STS 5-7 has already been completed and I \u0022just\u0022 need to execute the missions and edit the next video. A release can only be months away from now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChances are that I will get some time during the winter for more regular submissions here. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krazy1","CreatedById":203523,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-05T13:06:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s my sub for STS-1A and 1B. I flew it in my career game. I used TweakScale and Simple Fuel Switch - essential to the game IMO. I\u0027m glad you have a mod category.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the orbiter, I went berserk and used Whiplashes for full flight capability and precision landing, and NERVs to use this ship for later missions. It might \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E without cargo but I didn\u0027t try. I did a supersonic test flight from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E to the desert airfield with the 40t payload.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe booster is \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E recoverable. That\u0027s a self-imposed rule for all my builds now.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/J83omQa\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAlbum link\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope it\u0027s ok that I combined the albums. These 2 seem pretty straightforward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-06T14:30:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224062154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638709612\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203523\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krazy1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/5/2021 at 2:06 PM, Krazy1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s my sub for STS-1A and 1B. I flew it in my career game. I used TweakScale and Simple Fuel Switch - essential to the game IMO. I\u0027m glad you have a mod category.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the orbiter, I went berserk and used Whiplashes for full flight capability and precision landing, and NERVs to use this ship for later missions. It might \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E without cargo but I didn\u0027t try. I did a supersonic test flight from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E to the desert airfield with the 40t payload.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe booster is \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E recoverable. That\u0027s a self-imposed rule for all my builds now.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/J83omQa\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAlbum link\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope it\u0027s ok that I combined the albums. These 2 seem pretty straightforward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks good! Just for future refrence please don\u0027t combine multiple missions as it makes it harder to judge but this looks fine.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nHere you go, your badges!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022yPaylCw.png\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 width=\u0022125\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/yPaylCw.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022oVCWtIo.png\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 width=\u0022125\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/oVCWtIo.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"unolover322","CreatedById":217707,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-07T08:17:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif only the connecters weren\u0027t broken\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-07T08:43:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUh, what connecters?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krazy1","CreatedById":203523,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-07T01:08:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s my entry for 2A modded. I used basically the same design from 1b, so it was way oversized but Jeb liked it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/qQoP9pf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u0026gt; album \u0026lt;\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krazy1","CreatedById":203523,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-07T08:33:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here\u0027s 2B. It took 4 attempts to land... but I got it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/c3I2LoJ\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u0026gt; album for 2B \u0026lt;\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-08T17:25:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224087876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644196134\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203523\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krazy1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/7/2022 at 2:08 AM, Krazy1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s my entry for 2A modded. I used basically the same design from 1b, so it was way oversized but Jeb liked it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/qQoP9pf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u0026gt; album \u0026lt;\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongrats! Your badge has been granted\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mdMqDU4.png\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 width=\u0022125\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/mdMqDU4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224087973\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221644222808\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203523\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krazy1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/7/2022 at 9:33 AM, Krazy1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here\u0027s 2B. It took 4 attempts to land... but I got it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/c3I2LoJ\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u0026gt; album for 2B \u0026lt;\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou landed thats for sure, here\u0027s your badge!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022c5j8dvC.png\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 width=\u0022125\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/c5j8dvC.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits quite rare to recieve 2 badges at the same time (No it isn\u0027t) so i hope you feel special (You are not)!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krazy1","CreatedById":203523,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-12T04:26:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks (maybe)\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gamepuch","CreatedById":218149,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-16T15:11:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224dsj73rvq7i81.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022177.50\u0022 height=\u00221136\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.redd.it/4dsj73rvq7i81.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vdow16g3hsh81.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.redd.it/vdow16g3hsh81.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002279yh1h5040i81.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.redd.it/79yh1h5040i81.jpg\u0022\u003Eshuttle \u0022jay\u0022\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003Egot three Kerbals to station, I think pic of my test flight landing will ruin my take on challenge.(STS 1a)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-02-16T17:47:51Z\u0022 title=\u002202/16/2022 05:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 16, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by gamepuch\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Artienia","CreatedById":184444,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-17T13:03:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224092546\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221645024312\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218149\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gamepuch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, gamepuch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0shutte \u0022jay\u0022\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003Egot three Kerbals to station, I think pic of my test flight landing will ruin my take on challenge.(STS\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u0027m sorry but this isn\u0027t enough proof for the badge. Please create an imgur album for every stage of the flight. Thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gamepuch","CreatedById":218149,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-17T14:46:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224092978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221645103016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184444\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Artienia\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Artienia said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u0027m sorry but this isn\u0027t enough proof for the badge. Please create an imgur album for every stage of the flight. Thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngot it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sturmhauke","CreatedById":190611,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-02-17T17:56:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour orbiter is also required to land mostly intact. How much damage is somewhat subjective, but landing upside down with the wings sheared off is definitely too much. Basically that means the major airframe and heat-resistant components must survive reentry and landing. Missions that involve returning a payload must also have an intact payload. If you\u0027re not sure, please ask first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OJT","CreatedById":217353,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-12T02:53:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/190611-sturmhauke/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022190611\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/190611-sturmhauke/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sturmhauke\u003C/a\u003E. Nice challenge you\u0027ve got going on here\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m currently working on some stuff for this, but before doing any submissions I\u0027d like to clarify some things\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- Does the Launch System for the orbiter has to have structure like the actual STS System (as in, fuel tank and 2 SRBs) or am I allowed liberties on this one? And how far can I take it if I am allowed liberties? (from Buran-style Launcher with heavy lift rocket and 4 liquid fuel boosters to million Twin-Boars stuck to one another)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- In addition to that: must the Orbiter be mounted on the side or am I allowed to place it wherever I want to? Say, if it\u0027s narrow enough, can I place it on top of the rocket and build a fairing around it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- For missions STS-1b and STS-2b: it says those are Bonus missions, does it mean I can skip them if I want to? Because specifics of these missions mean that those are pretty much limited to Mk.3 style Orbiters and I had some promising Mk.2 designs in the works\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}